HEADWORD: Marmorated
<hw>Mar"mo*ra`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>marmoratus</ets>, p.
p. of <ets>marmorate</ets> to overlay with marble, fr. <ets>marmor</ets>
marble.]</ety> <def>Variegated like marble; covered or overlaid with
marble.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

